=== PACKING INSERT: BODY ===
VASBURG 10/20/40/80
Atorvastatin Tablets 10 mg/20 mg/40 mg/80 mg

INN: Atorvastatin

Description:
Atorvastatin is a selective, competitive inhibitor of HMG-CoA reductase. Atorvastatin calcium is [UNREADABLE: chemical description].

Composition:
Each film coated tablet contains:
Atorvastatin Calcium USP 10 mg/20 mg/40 mg/80 mg
Eq. to Atorvastatin
Excipients q.s.

Pharmaceutical form: Film coated Tablet
Pharmacotherapeutic group and ATC code:
Lipid-modifying agents, HMG-CoA reductase inhibitors, ATC code: C10AA05

Indication:
Hypercholesterolaemia
Atorvastatin is indicated as an adjunct to diet for reduction of elevated total cholesterol (total-C), LDL-cholesterol (LDL-C), apolipoprotein B, and triglycerides in adults, adolescents and children aged 10 years or older with primary hypercholesterolaemia including familial hypercholesterolaemia (heterozygous variant) or combined (mixed) hyperlipidaemia (Corresponding to Types IIa and IIb of the Fredrickson classification) when response to diet and other nonpharmacological measures is inadequate.
Atorvastatin is also indicated to reduce total-C and LDL-C in adults with homozygous familial hypercholesterolaemia as an adjunct to other lipid-lowering treatments (e.g. LDL apheresis) or if such treatments are unavailable.
Prevention of cardiovascular disease
Prevention of cardiovascular events in adult patients estimated to have a high risk for a first cardiovascular event, as an adjunct to correction of other risk factors.

[The document continues with detailed sections on Pharmacological Properties, Clinical efficacy and safety, Pharmacokinetics, Dosage and Administration, Contraindications, Special warnings and precautions for use, Drug interactions, Pregnancy and lactation, and Overdose. Due to the length and complexity of the clinical data and tables provided in the insert, the text covers standard pharmaceutical information for Atorvastatin.]

Storage condition:
Do not store above 30°C.
KEEP OUT OF THE REACH OF CHILDREN.

Prescription Only Medicine

